information for postdoctoral scholars information resources & technology irt stanford university school of medicine stanford university postdoctoral scholars search sites to search ways to give find a person alumni lane library ways to give find a person stanford postdoc handbook introduction welcome to stanford university where we have a thriving academic community which includes over 1800 postdoctoral scholars stanford prides itself on recruiting skilled and talented scholars from all over the country and is strongly committed to an affirmative action program for admitting qualified minority applicants for fellowship positions what is a postdoc a stanford postdoctoral scholar is a trainee in residence at stanford university pursuing advanced studies beyond the doctoral level in preparation for an independent career postdoctoral scholars are appointed for a limited period of time and may participate on stanford research projects and or may be supported by external awards or fellowships in all cases their appointment at stanford is for the purpose of advanced studies and training under the mentorship of a stanford faculty member this handbook is intended to provide key information scholars will need to get started survive and thrive at stanford university use the search handbook field or the table of contents links at left to find specific topics you are here current tab 3 stanford university postdocs handbook navigation for this section postdoc handbook introduction navigation for this section policy university policy rights and responsibilities on academic authorship diversity codes of conduct relationship between postdocs and outside entities and conflict of commitment and interest faculty policy on commitment and interest grievances visas funding guidelines navigation for this section professional development career planning educational programs training teaching and consulting auditing courses fellowships navigation for this section benefits health and benefits